-- Buckeye Makes `Temporary' Repairs on Illinois Crude Pipeline After Leak
-- B y   P a u l   B u r k h a r d t
-- 2010-12-15T12:52:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-15/buckeye-makes-temporary-repairs-on-illinois-crude-pipeline-after-leak.html
Buckeye Partners LP has made
“temporary” repairs to a 12-inch crude oil pipeline that was
shut after a leak near Romeoville, Illinois, said Colleen
Kester, a spokeswoman for the company. Buckeye is working with
regulators on a restart plan, she said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Paul Burkhardt in New York at 
